  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Specific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of the money through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the funds into the legitimate economy\n\nKey legal elements often include:\n- Knowingly concealing the origins of criminal proceeds\n- Attempting to make illegally obtained money appear legitimate\n- Engaging in financial transactions designed to hide the source of funds\n- Transferring money to disguise its illegal origins\n\nSpecific requirements and penalties vary by country and jurisdiction. For precise legal details, I recommend consulting local legal resources or a qualified attorney.",
